      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VYTIS (3) finished fourth at Listed level behind top mare Jilliby Ballerini when last seen at Ballarat in January, beaten 5.3 metres. He raced against the good three-year-olds last season, placing in the Breeders Crown Final the last time he raced here. Ideally drawn and should be ready to go off two nice trials. CRACKERJACK NZ (7) is a newcomer to the Russell Jack yard from NZ. Resumes from a spell of six months after closing off last campaign in good form, the last run being a solid second in the Golden Gait at Alexandra Park. Must overcome a very wide draw but has placed in all three fresh attempts and was readied with two trials. QUIRKY CHARACTER (8) has been tackling stronger races of late but this suits better and he owns a good record at this circuit and distance so looks for a better result. MUSKEE (4) must be included after winning his past two starts here, the latest from a wider draw. SEBASTIANS BOY (10) was readied with a trial win and goes well fresh so keep safe.",
